The government's decision:

Under the "Jal Jeevan Mission Programme," Dr. Matargaon Kh. , T. The Scheme for Shegaon Tap Water Supply Scheme has been given a price hike of Rs. 1 crore, subject to the following conditions, namely, increase in the Goods and Services Tax (GST) rate and increase in the tender rate of additional rate due to technical reasons. 53,60,650 - (Rupees fifty-three lakhs sixty thousand six hundred and fifty only) is being approved by the revised administrator.
Conditions
1) The CEO / Chief Engineer will be responsible for completing all the remaining works within the prescribed time frame at the above mentioned revised cost.
2) The terms and conditions mentioned while granting the revised technical approval as well as the original administrative approval agreed upon for the scheme should be strictly adhered to.

3) On completion of the scheme, it should be handed over to the concerned Gram Panchayat. The concerned Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad shall be responsible for taking over the scheme within one month from the date of receipt of intimation from the concerned Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zila Parishad that the scheme has actually been completed. Immediately after the actual completion of the scheme, a joint inspection of the scheme should be conducted by the concerned Executive Engineer, Zilla Parishad and concerned Gram Panchayat officials and any defects found in such inspection should be corrected before handing over the scheme.

4) The Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad concerned shall not receive any assistance from the Government for the implementation of the scheme, maintenance, repairs (including special modifications), depreciation in the scheme or for the renovation of machinery to meet the annual expenditure.
5) On completion of the scheme, it will be mandatory for the local body (concerned Gram Panchayat / Zila Parishad) to implement the scheme. The accounts of the scheme should also be closed.

6) According to a CAG report in 2013, 21 per cent of water supply schemes in the state have been shut down due to poor maintenance / non-payment of electricity bills due to lack of these maintenance repairs. In fact, in order to make the scheme more efficient, it will be the responsibility of the concerned Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad to increase the water table rate as per requirement.
7) Action should be taken in accordance with the prevailing policy on extortion.
8) It shall be the responsibility of the Zilla Parishad that the present scheme shall not be revised under any circumstances.
